    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for one four-player source round where three separate forced wall-death updates leave avatar 1 as the sole round-end survivor, then warmdown continues to the next source round.",
      "The harness starts a real source round, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, holds avatar 1 on a slow safe path, then forces avatars 4, 3, and 2 into wall deaths across separate Game.update(100) calls at the same source timestamp.",
      "The separate terminal updates prove source death-order scoring: the dead avatars receive 0, 1, and 2 round points, then avatar 1 receives the 4P survivor bonus.",
      "Bonuses are disabled so the pinned random stream contains spawn and PrintManager distances only."
    ]
  },
